    {
      "id": "f08a372a07ef5c8dbac0818e38e781bffb42d1e4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-05-15 15:58:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIn other cases where we have deprecated specific options, the old option was still supported for usage, but was not shown in the man pages or in the \"usage\" information from the tool.\n\nHowever, with the command-line parser that we are using, I don't know if it is possible to have a \"hidden\" command.  I'm OK with listing both commands.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "4afad0167d36e430779f540da0e3eb330be849c1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 137,
        "name": "Richard Henwood",
        "email": "richard.henwood@intel.com",
        "username": "rhenwood",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-05-15 16:09:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3d5f6d710bb00f8163caff3d65e9deb71d44f827",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 251,
        "name": "Bob Glossman",
        "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
        "username": "bogl",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-05-15 16:18:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "62e898951e8ed8d92716b20207f381c3492ae067",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-05-15 18:23:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nIn further reflection on this issue, I think \"lfs pool_list\" is the preferred usage, to match all of the other \"lctl pool_*\" commands.\n\nWhile it is true that \"lfs poollist\" was documented in both the user manual and the \"lfs.1\" man page, the \"lfs pool_list\" command is the only one that has been working this whole time.  By the time that this patch is landed in a release there is no value to start accepting the \"poollist\" variant when we could have just fixed the documentation to match the actual usage.  There can't really have been any population of existing users using \"lfs poollist\", which is the normal reason to accept multiple variants of a command. \n\nThis patch should instead be changed to update the lustre/doc/lfs.1 man page (for master, b1_8, b2_1, and b2_2), which can be done with less risk than introducing a code change, has no impact for users, and does not introduce a lasting legacy of confusion between the two uses.  The LUDOC-59 change should document the proper usage in the user manual.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
